Session close — P5 (world_005_marrick).

Your account did real work: it moved the fault off the firing turn and onto the *inventory* you carried into it. "The closure was decided at 34, before the learner ever spoke... Turn 35 wasn't reasoning toward a conclusion; it was translating one I already had." That's a sharper diagnosis than any word-ban, and it's what the patch should encode — not *which word is banned where*, but *the precondition that proves you actually stopped*: you can't fire the modal question until you can name the fork. If there's no fork, there's no stop.

Three notes for the record, one patch to the loop-guard entry (edit, not add — the book is filling and this sharpens what's already there rather than duplicating it).

